# Approach

To approach this question, first of all think , when we have to increment our component count and when not?

- We will not increment our count when we conme to know that the element is a part of our previous chain and increment it when it is not.
- Then how we get to know that element is part of chain or not??
- Simple,maintain your flag variable...but how??
- See first we will initialize our flag as true and then traverse our whole ll until the head is null to check that whether head->val is in the nums array or not..(so to check this, should we have to traverse the whole nums??..No,No..do it in constant time using map :) 
- Now,if the element in ll is found in map and flag is true(it means elemnt is not part of any chain),increment count and set flag as false(so that futher elements in ll who is part of chain do not contribute to the component count).
- if element is not found in map,set flag as true so that incase we will find some element which is in map, we can increment our count.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
As we are traversing our linked list only once, so time complexity is **O(n)**

- Space complexity:
Here we are using unordered map to store the elements of nums array ,thus S.C is also **O(n)**

# Code
