**Idea**
Basically counting all the starting points of the chains. First while loop gets you to start of the chain, next while loop gets you to a node just past the end of the chain.

```
public int numComponents(ListNode head, int[] g) {
        Set<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();
        for(int i : g)
            set.add(i);
        int count = 0;
        while(head != null){
            while(head != null && !set.contains(head.val)){
                head = head.next;
            }
            //new chain starting point
            if(head != null) ++count;
            while(head != null && set.contains(head.val)){
                set.remove(head.val);
                head = head.next;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
```

