Steps:
1. Add all the integer array elements to a HashSet (for easy O(1) access).
2. Traverse the Linked List. Check if an element exists in the hashset.
3. If it does exist: If not counted previuosly, Assign prev_counted to true now and increse your counter (res). 
4. If it doesn't exist, change it back to false (Starting fresh).
5. Keep traversing until the end of the Linked List.
6. Return the result (res).


```
class Solution {
    public int numComponents(ListNode head, int[] G) {
        if(head==null) return 0;
        HashSet<Integer> hs=new HashSet<Integer>();
        int res=0;
        boolean prev_counted=false;
        for(int num:G) hs.add(num);

        ListNode curr=head;
        while(curr!=null)
        {
            int val=curr.val;
            if(hs.contains(val))
            {
                if(!prev_counted) 
                {
                   res++;
                   prev_counted=true;
                }
            }
            else
            {
                prev_counted=false;
            }
            curr=curr.next;
        }
        return res;  
    }
}

