solutions.content:
We maintain a hashmap to store all the nodes that have the same cummulative sum. The cummulative sum is the key, and the list of all nodes that has this cummulative sum is the value.
We travserse the linked list. For each node, we iterate through all the previous nodes that have the current cummulative sum and remove all nodes between. Then we update the list of nodes that has the same cummulative sum and put the list into map.
```
public ListNode removeZeroSumSublists(ListNode head) {
        Map<Integer, List<ListNode>> map = new HashMap<>();
        ListNode dummy = new ListNode(0);
        dummy.next = head;
        int sum = 0;
        List<ListNode> first = new ArrayList<>(0);
        first.add(dummy);
        map.put(sum, first);
        ListNode curr = head;
        while (curr != null){
            sum += curr.val;
            List<ListNode> prevs = map.getOrDefault(sum, new ArrayList<>());
            for(ListNode prev : prevs) {
                prev.next = curr.next;    
            }
            prevs.add(curr);
            map.put(sum, prevs);
            curr = curr.next;
        }
        return dummy.next;
    }

```

