```
/*
Approach: Keep a running sum upto everynode in a map, if the sum already exist in the map, then everything from the previous map value to current map value sums to zero and can be deleted from linked list. At the same time, we will remove the deleted nodes from map as well to prevent checking a deleted node sum.

Example:
               a b c d  e  f g  i j
Input: head = [1,3,2,-3,-2,5,5,-5,1]

Output: a f j
The map would be constructed as:

1 : a
4: b
6: c
3: d
1: e ----- we need to delete everything from last seen 1(a) to 1(e), otherwise 6(c) would be double counted for "f" below
6:f
11:g
6:i ------- same thing, delete from "f"
7:j

0 == delete upto current from head and take next node as head
if not, 
    check if we have seen this sum before, if we have, then that must mean everything in between must sum to zero. e.g. (b+c+d+e)
else,
    add the running sum with the assosiated node in the map

Analysis: Linear time and space

*/
class Solution {
    public ListNode removeZeroSumSublists(ListNode head) {
        if(head == null){
            return head;
        }

        Map<Integer, ListNode> sumNodeMap = new HashMap<>();

        int sum = 0;
        ListNode node = head;
        while(node != null){
            sum += node.val;

            if(sum == 0){
                int presum = 0;
                removeSumStartsWith(head, node, presum, sumNodeMap); //update map
                head = node.next; //update linked list
            }else if(sumNodeMap.containsKey(sum)){
                ListNode pre = sumNodeMap.get(sum);
                int presum = sum;

                removeSumStartsWith(pre.next, node, presum, sumNodeMap); //update map
                pre.next = node.next; //update linked list
            } else {
                sumNodeMap.put(sum, node);
            }

            node = node.next;
        }
        return head;
    }

    private void removeSumStartsWith(ListNode start, ListNode end, int presum, Map<Integer, ListNode> sumNodeMap) {
        while(start != end) {
            presum += start.val;
            sumNodeMap.remove(presum);
            start = start.next;
        }
    }
}
