Code using permutation 
We have total n places to fill with 5 vowels to fill with.In short we have n identical thigs to be distributed among 5 people for which the formulae is 
(n+5-1)C(5-1)= (n+4)C4=(n+1)*(n+2)*(n+3)*(n+4)/24
```
class Solution {
public:
    int countVowelStrings(int n) {
        /// We can assume that there would be 4 transition states 
        /// Ie from a->e->i->o->u
        /// and along with these transitions there would be n vowels in sorted order
        /// hence we have total n+4 locations and after choosing 4 of them 
        /// (for the transitions to take place)
        /// the elements at all other positions got fixed 
        /// hence the answer is n+4 C 4.
        return (n+1)*(n+2)*(n+3)*(n+4)/24;
    }
};
```
