solutions.content:
### **As you scroll down, there is a optimized solution given than the previous one.**

* #####  **Approach-1**: **Recursion** *(Shows **TLE for n>40 and works for n<=40**)*

Here, every next call for a decreased value of n gives us the required result and then we will add vowels at the start of result we get to get the strings of desired length. ( **i.e for n=2**, solver(n-1) or here, **solver(1) gives us the sorted vowels strings of length=1** and then we will **add up vowels again at the start of the sorted vowels strings we get, (maintaining the lexicographically sorted order) to get the sorted vowels strings of length=2**) 

***-->CODE:***
```
class Solution
{
private:
    vector<char> vowels = {'a', 'e', 'i', 'o', 'u'};
public:
    vector<string> solver(int n)
    {
        if (n == 0)
        return {""};

        vector<string> asf = solver(n - 1);
        vector<string> ans;

        for (string i : asf)
        {
            for (char j : vowels)
            {
			 	//check that the character you want to insert 
				//is smaller than the first character of asf(answer so far) string 
				//to maintain lexicographically sorted order
                if (j <= i[0] || asf.size() == 1)
                    ans.push_back(j + i);
                else
                    break;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
    int countVowelStrings(int n)
    {
        vector<string> ans = solver(n);
        return ans.size();
    }
};
```

* #####  **Approach-2**: **Backtrack** *(**Gets submitted**)*

***-->CODE:***
```
 void solver(vector<vector<char>> &ans, vector<char> &temp, vector<char> &vowels, int start, int n)
    {
        if (temp.size() == n)
        {   ans.push_back(temp);
            return;
        }

        for (int i = start; i < vowels.size(); i++)
        {
            temp.push_back(vowels[i]);
            solver(ans, temp, vowels, i, n);
            temp.pop_back();
        }
        return;
    }

    int countVowelStrings(int n)
    {   vector<char> vowels = {'a', 'e', 'i', 'o', 'u'};
        vector<char> temp;
        vector<vector<char>> ans;
        solver(ans, temp, vowels, 0, n);
        return ans.size();
    }
```

* ##### **Approach-3**: Dynamic Programming(**DP**), **Time:O(n), Space:O(n)**
-Here, you can observe: 
```
n=1, dp = {1,2,3,4,5}      return 5
n=2, dp = {1,3,6,10,15}    return 15
n=3, dp = {1,4,10,20,35}   return 35
```

