```

* ##### **Approach-4:**  **Time:O(n), Space:O(1)**

-Here, you can observe a pattern : 
```
		   a  e  i  o  u
 ->  n=1   1  1  1  1  1  
 ->  n=2   5  4  3  2  1  
 ->  n=3   15 10 6  3  1
```

If we observe every other element will have the count of previous count value + next element count for the same n. As example
n=2,  a(in n=1) + count of next element, i.e e(in n=2) =5
n=3,  e(in n=2) + count of next element, i.e i(in n=3) =10

***-->CODE:***
   ```
 int countVowelStrings(int n)
    {
        int a, e, i, o, u;
        a = e = i = o = u = 1;
        while (--n)
        {
            o += u;
            i += o;
            e += i;
            a += e;
        }
        return a + e + i + o + u;
    }
```

