solutions.content:
It is an awesome problem. Lets deep dive in it.

So, they are asking the number of ways in which we can generate  lexographically sorted strings of length n, which only contains vowels.

Now lets think about it.
Suppose if  `n=1` then the possible strings would be ```"a","e","i","o","u"```.


Now lets make an approach.

Lets create a 2-D array of size 5 * n and for our example lets take ```n=3```
So here is our array.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/5cfacf83-2f89-4369-9fd6-c9d1b01d3f6a_1652281456.4877005.jpeg)

Here we will store the number of strings we that will end on respective vowel for the given n.
Now for n=1, all the values will be 1.

Lets fill it for n=2.
For string to be ending on ```a``` we have only one way i.e all the characters will be ```'a'```.

For string  to be ending on ```b``` we have two options that either append ```'b'``` on string which previously ended on ```a``` or append ```'b'``` to the string which previously ended on ```b```.

For string to be ending on ```c``` we have three options that we append ```'c'``` on string ending with ```a``` or ```b``` or append ```'c'``` to the string which previously ended on ```c```.

It hope you got the idea :)

Now lets fill our array.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/c5cf43d8-ae70-47b7-afba-eb7e3f9c7394_1652282112.450616.jpeg)

At last the sum of last column will be our answer.

Awesome we solved it !!!

But can we do better? Can we do it in O(1) space?

If you look closely we are only using the previous values of the column. So there is no need to use this array we will replace it by 5 variables which will be storing the content of column values.

Here is my code :

```
class Solution {
    public int countVowelStrings(int n) {
        int a=1,e=1,i=1,o=1,u=1;
        for(int index=1;index<n;index++){
            int aNew=a,eNew=a+e,iNew=a+e+i,oNew=a+e+i+o,uNew=a+e+i+o+u;
            a=aNew;
            e=eNew;
            i=iNew;
            o=oNew;
            u=uNew;
        }
        return a+e+i+o+u;
    }
}
```

