```
/*

EXPLANATION: [C++]-1 LINER-EASY TO UNDERSTAND-BEGINNER-SHORT CONCISE-INTERVIEW-WITH EXPLANATION

EXPLANATION:

Basically n==1 - 5 combinations. Each ending with a vowel

ending with a-5,e-4,i-3,o-2,u-1
n==2 = 5+4+3+2+1

similarly n==3 == 35... 15+ (aa-5 , ae-4, ai-3,ao-2, au-1 and so on), which will lead to binomial coefficient of Binomial coefficient binomial(n,4) = n*(n-1)*(n-2)*(n-3)/24 starting from 5th term

Thus follows https://oeis.org/A000332
*/

class Solution {
public:
    int countVowelStrings(int n) {
        return ((n+4)*(n+3)*(n+2)*(n+1))/24;
    }
};
```

