solutions.content:
***Method 1 - (Using Backtracking)***

Solution Idea: 
1. We first create a vector storing all the vowels present in English alphabets.
2. We the create a function called *helper* which contains the backtracking algo.
3. The code has been further commented in each part, for better understanding.

```
class Solution {

    int count = 0;
    vector<int> word = {'a', 'e', 'i', 'o', 'u'}; //vector containg all the 5 vowels.

    void helper(string &s, int n) // string s contains the answer string.
    {
        if(s.size() == n)
          count++; // if the size of s reaches n (given in the problem), we increase count value by 1.

        for(int i=0;i<=4;i++)
        { // iterating over all the elements of vector word.
            if(s.size() == 0)
            { // initially, when answer string s in empty, we directly put the letter from word vector, and later perform backtracking.
				s.push_back(word[i]);
				helper(s, n);
				s.pop_back();
			}

			else if(s.size()<n && s.back()<=word[i])
			{ // else if size of answer string is greater than 0, but not yet equal to n, and also **the last letter of the string s, is less than the current letter**,
			  // we push the current letter in the answer string and do the backtracking as usual.
				s.push_back(word[i]);
				helper(s, n);
				s.pop_back();
			}
        }
    }
public:
    int countVowelStrings(int n)
    {
        string s ;
        helper(s, n);
        return count; // returning count value as answer.
    }
};
```
**Time Complexity = O(5^n)**. 
For every letter out of n, we have 5 possibilities.
****
***Method 2 - (Mathematical Pattern)***

Solution Idea: 
 Basic idea is to observe a patern amongst the relationship between the given value of n, and the output.

Some observations - 
	1. For n=1, output is 5.
	2. For n=2, output is 15. 
	   By Triangle number formula, putting N=5 in
	   [ N*(N+1) ]/ [1* 2], we get 15.   
	3. For n=3, output is 35.
	  Putting N=5, in 
	 [ N*(N+1)* (N+2) ]/ [ 1* 2* 3 ]


So, for any value n:
we put N=5 in the formula - 

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/953ab72b-8cd5-4c16-aa4a-a57433a47c1a_1612279954.0210714.png)


Hence we arrive at our needed expression.	
```  
class Solution {   
public:
    int countVowelStrings(int n)
    {
        return (n+1)*(n+2)*(n+3)*(n+4)/24;
    }
};
```
**Time Complexity = O(1)**.
****

View more solutions [HERE](https://github.com/noob-hu-yaar/Leetcode/tree/master/nandincpp)
