solutions.content:
# Intuition
we have to form all permuntation of vowels of length n. we can consider 5 vowel in number as 0 to 4. In recursive approach we have to once iterate till n for count and till 4 to change every character of vowel

# Approach
BaseCase for recursive function will be 
```        
if(count>=n){
    return 1;
}
if(vowel>=5){
    return 0;
}
```

And as i explained we need to perform 2 operations
```
// For increasing vowel
int f1=f(vowel+1,count,n,dp);

// For increasing count 
int f2=f(vowel,count+1,n,dp);

return f1+f2

```

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
(n*5)

- Space complexity:
O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:

    int f(int vowel,int count,int n,vector<vector<int>> &dp){
        if(count>=n){
            return 1;
        }
        if(vowel>=5){
            return 0;
        }

        if(dp[count][vowel]!=-1) return dp[count][vowel];

        int f1=f(vowel+1,count,n,dp);
        int f2=f(vowel,count+1,n,dp);

        return dp[count][vowel]=f1+f2;
    }

    int countVowelStrings(int n) {
        vector<vector<int>> dp(n+1,vector<int>(5,-1));
        return f(0,0,n,dp);
    }
};
```

