**Using Dynamic Programming** 
* The Pattern we can observe for this problem.
# 	
          a  e  i  o  u 
    n=1   1  1  1  1  1  /a, e, i, o, u
    n=2   5  4  3  2  1  /a-> aa,ae,ai,ao,au | e-> ee,ei,eo,eu | i-> ii,io,iu | o-> oo,ou | u-> uu
    n=3   15 10 6  3  1
* If we observe from last there will be only 1 element which will start with u. 
* Every other element will have the count of previous count + next element count.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int countVowelStrings(int n) {

        // Here we’re taking a vector of 5 sizes and initialising with 1.
        vector<int> dp(5,1) ;
        int ans = 0 ;

        while( --n ){

            // Iterating from the 2nd last & add the next element to the present element.
            // Observe the Pattern for more clarification 
            for( int i=3 ; i>=0 ; i-- ){
                dp[i] += dp[i+1];
            }
        }

        // Return the sum of every vector element.
        for( auto it : dp ) ans += it ;
        return ans ;
    }
};
```

