solutions.content:
**Idea:** There will be two dp states n and m.
* n : represents how many letters left to fullfill the word from this state.
* m : represents the number of vowel left from this state.
* base case : for all i = 1 - n, dp[i][0] will be 1.
* base case : for all i = 1 - 5, dp[0][i] will be 0.

Complexity: O(n * n * 5)

Recursive code:
```
class Solution {
public:
    int dp[55][6];
    int countVowelStrings(int n) {
        for(int i=0;i<=n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<=5;j++){
                dp[i][j] = -1;
            }
        }
        return call(n, 5);
    }

    int call(int n, int m){
        if(n==0) return 1;
        if(m==0) return 0;

        if(dp[n][m] != -1){
            return dp[n][m];
        }

        int res = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<=n;i++){
            res += call(n - i, m - 1);
        }

        return dp[n][m] = res;
    }
};
```

