Here CountA represents words starting with vowel A.
CountE represents words starting with vowel E and so on.
For length n, we are storing all these counts for no. of strings starting with particular vowel.
To calculate for n+1 length, we can simply use these formulaes,
`countA=countA+countE+countI+countO+countU` bcz vowel A can be added in all cases for length n.
`countE=countE+countI+countO+countU` bcz vowel E can only be added for all length n strings with starting vowel E, I, O, U
and so on.

