There is a simple logic behind this approach which is as follows,
* To make string of **length n** which starts with **"a"** can be formed by concating strings of **length n-1** which can start with **{a,e,i,o,u}**.
* To make string of **length n** which starts with **"e"** can be formed by concating strings of **length n-1** which can start with **{e,i,o,u}**.
* To make string of **length n** which starts with **"i"** can be formed by concating strings of **length n-1** which can start with **{i,o,u}**.
* To make string of **length n** which starts with **"o"** can be formed by concating strings of **length n-1** which can start with **{o,u}**.
* To make string of **length n** which starts with **"u"** can be formed by concating strings of **length n-1** which can start with **{u}**.

