The main important point is that:
If the numbers with negative sign are even, than all can be converted to postitive numbers.
If the numbers with negative sign are odd, than one will be left negative and others can be converted to positive.
Also, in case of odd no. of negative numbers, we can make all numbers positive and make smallest number negative, in order to maximise the sum.
```
class Solution {
    public long maxMatrixSum(int[][] matrix) {
        long ans = 0;
        int neg = 0;
        int min = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for(int i = 0; i < matrix.length; i++){
            for(int j = 0; j < matrix[0].length; j++){
                if(matrix[i][j] < 0) {
                    neg++;
                }
                ans += Math.abs(matrix[i][j]);
                if(min > Math.abs(matrix[i][j]))
                	min = Math.abs(matrix[i][j]);
            }
        }
        if(neg % 2 == 0)
        	return ans;
        else
        	return ans - 2*min;
    }
}
```
