Looking at the flip operations we have, we can always invert the current cell + a neightbor. We can also invert using two actions any cell + neighbor of neighbor (the neighbor itself gets flipped twice). We can therefore infer that we can flip any pair => the sum will be the sum over the positive matrix minus the smalles negative number * 2, if the pairity is odd, or 0 when the parity is even.

```ts
function maxMatrixSum(matrix: number[][]): number {
    let min = 100_000;
    let sum = 0;
    let parity = 0
    for (let row of matrix) {
        for (let x of row) {
            if (x < 0) {
                parity += 1;
                x = -x
            }
            min = Math.min(x, min);
            sum += x
        } 
    }
    return sum - (2 * min * (parity%2));
};
```

