If we have *even* number of negative items we can turn all of them into positive; in this case we can just sum all the items of the `matrix`. If we have *odd* number of negative items we can turn all but arbitrary one into positive; let this *arbitrary* one be the minimum by absolute value:

```
public class Solution {
    public long MaxMatrixSum(int[][] matrix) {
        bool even = true;

        int min = int.MaxValue;

        long result = 0;

        foreach (int[] line in matrix) {
            foreach (int v in line) {
                result += Math.Abs(v);

                min = Math.Min(min, Math.Abs(v));

                if (v < 0)
                    even = !even;
            }
        }    

        if (even)
            return result;

        return result - 2 * min;
    }
}
```

